ns0:DescribedValueSet.ns0:Purpose: (Clinical Focus: This grouping of value sets contains concepts that represent a fetus in an abnormal position in the uterus at the time of delivery.),(Data Element Scope: This value set may use Quality Data Model (QDM) category related to Diagnosis or Encounter Performed (diagnosis attribute).The intent of this data element is to identify patients with a fetus in an abnormal position in the uterus at the time of delivery.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes only relevant concepts associated with codes that identify a fetus in an abnormal position (i.e. breech, brow, face, shoulder presentation). This is a grouping of ICD-10-CM and SNOMED CT codes.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude concepts that pertain to a fetus in a vertex presentation.)
